1
00:00:06,989 --> 00:00:09,189
Our business is joy.

2
00:00:09,209 --> 00:00:15,371
The hard work we do goes into building tiny machines of joy.

3
00:00:16,531 --> 00:00:19,871
We build, package, and ship joy.

4
00:00:21,772 --> 00:00:25,352
Our ultimate goal, regardless of how much we argue, stress,

5
00:00:25,612 --> 00:00:27,533
and struggle, and God knows we do,

6
00:00:28,353 --> 00:00:29,993
is to bring joy into the world.

7
00:00:31,233 --> 00:00:35,474
We are all part of the joy industrial complex.

8
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:41,522
As game developers, the fruit of our labor is joy.

9
00:00:43,163 --> 00:00:47,405
If an industry can have a soul, ours is joy.

10
00:00:51,007 --> 00:00:52,407
So how can it be so hard?

11
00:00:53,688 --> 00:00:55,889
How can it be so hard sometimes to get up in the morning?

12
00:00:56,349 --> 00:00:58,571
How can it be so hard to keep a studio running,

13
00:00:59,171 --> 00:01:03,393
to find job security, personal health, or even a decent wage?

14
00:01:05,294 --> 00:01:06,795
How can it be so hard?

15
00:01:09,492 --> 00:01:11,614
And how can we make the struggle easier?

16
00:01:12,074 --> 00:01:14,196
We are fragile and frail people.

17
00:01:15,056 --> 00:01:17,258
Sometimes we fall, sometimes we fail.

18
00:01:18,379 --> 00:01:20,641
But we are also capable of deep compassion

19
00:01:21,161 --> 00:01:22,322
and sublime empathy.

20
00:01:23,163 --> 00:01:25,204
And we always aim for joy.

21
00:01:27,606 --> 00:01:28,687
My name is Henrik Jansson,

22
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:30,468
and I will be your moderator today.

23
00:01:31,689 --> 00:01:33,751
The questions asked here are what we will discuss

24
00:01:33,951 --> 00:01:34,631
during the panel.

25
